---
description: ClevScaffold core rules — always applied
alwaysApply: true
---

Canonical guide: [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md). Topic docs in `docs/agents/` —
`nestjs.md` for any backend code, `recipes.md` for any multi-step task.

Non-negotiables:
- Ship tests with every code change; keep coverage ≥ 90% (jest enforces it).
  Prove done with `npm run verify` (plus `npm run e2e` for backend behaviour).
- No secrets in code/JSON/logs. No direct `process.env` — use `ConfigService`.
- No `any` (use `unknown` + narrowing). Explicit return types on exports. One class per file.
- Exact-pinned dependencies, added to the package that imports them (never the root);
  commit the lockfile in the same change.
- Guards by default; opt out only with `@Public()`. Derive identity from the JWT, never the body.
- No mock/fake data — real providers, explicit fallback or 503 when unconfigured.
- Use the shipped libs (capability map in AGENTS.md): config, logger, auth, pagination,
  Redis, metrics, crypto, messaging, feature-flags, compliance — never reimplement one.
  New personal data → register a `PersonalDataContributor`; sensitive mutations →
  `auditService.record(...)` (ids/field names in metadata, never PII values).
- Never guess: verify every file, symbol, route, env key, command, and package against
  the repo before referencing it. Code beats docs — flag drift, don't "fix" working code.
- Keep `clevscaffold:*:start/end` sentinel comment pairs intact (init.mjs prunes on them).
  The `clevscaffold:` prefix is the pruning marker, NOT the npm scope — never rename it.

When a gate fails, the code is wrong — not the gate. Never: lower coverage thresholds,
skip/delete failing tests, add unexplained `eslint-disable`/`@ts-ignore`, loosen
ValidationPipe/tsconfig/guards, or use `--force`/`--legacy-peer-deps`.

Stop and ask (full trigger list in AGENTS.md) before anything outside these docs:
new deps/libs/patterns, guardrail files, destructive migrations or API removals,
auth/compliance weakening, CI/deploy/init.mjs changes, or instructions that conflict
with the docs. Ask with: need, blocking rule, proposal, blast radius. Flagged
deviations are fine, silent ones never.

Stack: NestJS 11 · Nx · Node 22 · Postgres · TypeORM (apps/api) + Prisma 7 with the
pg driver adapter (apps/api-prisma) · Vite + Next frontends.
Config is layered: process.env → config/{NODE_ENV}.json → config/default.json → code default.
